# Single source of truth (app/)

When changing battle, pricing, formatting, or status behavior, update **one** canonical module — never copy logic into pages or components.

## Battle week (current display week)

| Need | Use |
|------|-----|
| Full context for home, sidebar, submit | `getHomeBattleWeek()` → `HomeBattleWeek` |
| Week enabled, min projects, submit price | `resolveEffectiveWeekSettings()` in `get-battle-week-settings-for-year.ts` |
| DB row → settings object | `mapBattleWeekSettingsRow()` in `map-battle-week-settings-row.ts` |
| ISO week math | `battle-week.ts` |
| Timing, status, badges, shuffle gate | `battle-week-status.ts` (`getBattleWeekTiming`, `resolveBattleWeekDisplayStatus`, `shouldShuffleBeforeVoting`, `displayStatusToBattlePhase`, `formatBattleStartHoursLabel`) |
| Leaderboard order / shuffle | `build-leaderboard.ts` (`prepareProductFeedOrder`, `buildLeaderboard`, `buildLeaderboardInFixedOrder`) |

```typescript
// BAD — site default only, ignores per-week settings
const { battleSubmitPrice } = await getSiteSettings();

// GOOD — same week + price + min projects as home hero
const homeBattleWeek = await getHomeBattleWeek();
```

Never hardcode `20 projects`, `24h`, or site-only prices in UI when `getHomeBattleWeek()` exists.

## Formatting

| Need | Use |
|------|-----|
| Points label (`1 point` / `5 points`) | `formatDisplayPoints()` |
| Points numeric input value | `formatPointsAmount()` |
| Money | `formatDisplayMoney()` |
| Money + points | `formatDisplayMoneyWithPoints()` |
| Dates / times | `format-display-date.ts` + user/site merge helpers |

See also `site-currency-formats.mdc` and `site-date-time-formats.mdc`.

## Before adding logic

1. Search `app/lib/` for an existing helper.
2. Extend the canonical function if the rule belongs there.
3. Pass `HomeBattleWeek` (or a typed slice) into components — do not re-fetch or re-derive the same fields in multiple places.

## SSR + random order

Shuffle on the **server** (`prepareProductFeedOrder` in `page.tsx`), pass the snapshot to client components. Never `Math.random()` in client `useState` for initial render order.
